==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mediastinum
<hw>Me`di*as*ti"num</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. <ets>mediastinum</ets>,
fr. L. <ets>medius</ets> middle; cf. <ets>mediastinus</ets> helper, a
menial servant, LL. <ets>mediastinus</ets> equiv. to <ets>medius</ets>:
cf F. <ets>m⟦eacute⟧diastin</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A
partition; a septum; specifically, the folds of the pleura (and the
space included between them) which divide the thorax into a right and
left cavity. The space included between these folds of the pleura,
called the <xex>mediastinal space</xex>, contains the heart and gives
passage to the esophagus and great blood vessels.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mediate</ent>⟦br⟧
